<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4268.1.1>
    bibo:endPage "33" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "4268" ;
    dc:creator "Lopes, Leonardo Esteves; Vasconcelos, Marcelo Ferreira De; Gonzaga, Luiz Pedreira" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "A cryptic new species of hummingbird of the Campylopterus largipennis complex (Aves: Trochilidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579861>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579862>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579860>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579855>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579863>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579864>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579865>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579866> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579861>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. The newly described Campylopterus calcirupicola (Dry-forest Sabrewing) from eastern Brazilian tropical dry forests. From an original watercolor painting by Walter Gam." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579862>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Two views of a young male of Campylopterus calcirupicola captured on 18 July 2006 in the Fazenda Corredor (880 m asl), municipality of Bocaiúva, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUFMG 5005). Photographs by LEL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579862/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579860>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Under right side of tail showing coloration pattern in taxa of the Campylopterus largipennis complex. Illustration composed of photographs of several museum specimens collected in the following areas of endemism: C. l. obscurus (Belém), C. l. aequatorialis (Napo), C. l. largipennis (Guiana), C. l. diamantinensis (Central Brazilian hills and tablelands) and “ Dry forest ” specimens (deciduous forests of Minas Gerais and Goiás). Photographs by LEL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579860/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579855>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Sexual dimorphism in the shape and size of bill (A) and in wing shape (B) of taxa in the Campylopterus largipennis complex. In both pictures male is presented above female. (A) male (MZUSP 99025, paratype) and female (MZUSP 99024, holotype). (B) male (DZUFMG 5007) and female (DZUFMG 7170). Photographs by LEL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579855/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579863>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Geographic distribution of the examined specimens of the Campylopterus largipennis complex. Light grey areas are covered by forests (Olson et al. 2001). Dark grey areas indicate elevations above 1,500 m asl. Letters “ T ” indicate type localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579864>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Detailed geographic distribution of Campylopterus calcirupicola (squares) and C. diamantinensis (triangles) in the state of Minas Gerais, eastern Brazil. In addition to the specimens examined, sight records are indicated by a dot inside the symbol. Higher altitudes are indicated by darker grey shading." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579864/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579865>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. The typical habitat of Campylopterus calcirupicola. Dry forest growing on limestone outcrop during the wet (left, late December) and dry (right, early October) seasons. Photographs taken in the municipality of Januária, Minas Gerais, Brazil, by LEL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579865/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.579866>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. The typical habitat of Campylopterus diamantinensis. Clockwise, from upper left: Serra do Breu (dry season), Parque Nacional das Sempre Vivas (wet season), and two pictures from Serra do Cipó (wet season). All photographs taken in Minas Gerais, Brazil, by Guilherme H. S. Freitas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/579866/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

